                        <div data-role="collapsible">
                            <h3>Business rates holiday for retail, hospitality and leisure businesses</h3>
                            <div data-role="collapsible"><h3>what is a business rates holiday for retail, hospitality and leisure businesses?</h3>Businesses in the retail, hospitality and leisure sectors in England will not have to pay business rates for the 2020 to 2021 tax year.</div>
                            <div data-role="collapsible">
                                <h3>Am I eligible for the business rates holiday for retail, hospitality and leisure businesses?</h3>
                                You’re eligible if your property is a:
                                <ol>
                                    <li>shop</li>
                                    <li>restaurant, café, bar or pub</li>
                                    <li>cinema or live music venue</li>
                                    <li>assembly or leisure property - for example, a sports club, a gym or a spa</li>
                                    <li>hospitality property - for example, a hotel, a guest house or self-catering accommodation</li>
                                </ol>
                            </div>
                            <div data-role="collapsible">
                                <h3>How do I apply for the business rates holiday for retail, hospitality and leisure businesses?</h3>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>You do not need to take any action. Your local council will apply the discount automatically.</li>
                                    <li>You can estimate the business rate relief using the business rates calculator https://www.gov.uk/calculate-your-business-rates.</li>
                                    <li>Contact your local council if you’re not getting a relief you think you’re entitled to. https://www.gov.uk/contact-your-local-council-about-business-rates
                                </ol>
